<p>I am a graduate student in <a href="http://web.mit.edu/physics/">the Physics Department</a> and <a href="http://space.mit.edu/">Kavli Institute</a> at Massachusetts Institute of Technology. This is my professional website about the my research and my other interests.</p>

<p>I study galaxy clusters, the largest known gravitationally bound structures in the universe. My current project involves identifying Phoenix-like clusters through cross-correlating all-sky survey datas, including ROSAT (X-ray), 2MASS (Near IR), WISE, (Mid IR), NVSS/SUMSS (Radio).</p>

